<html lang="en">
  <body>
    <p>
      You can test that <code>responseWriterCustomized</code> uses
      <code>fileError</code> to make a response for an error by issuing
      <code>http.StatusNotFound</code> and asserting it writes the content of
      this file.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can test that <code>file.ServeHTTP</code> uses
      <code>responseWriterCustomized</code> to customize error responses by
      requesting invalid path such as <code>/invalid</code> and asserting it
      writes the content of this file.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can test that <code>file.ServeHTTP</code> responses with
      <code>http.StatusNotFound</code> and the customized error message for
      <code>/index</code> by requesting <code>/index</code> and confirming it
      writes the content of this file.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
